	abstract = {There is a great lack of accessible entertainment options for low vision and blind people, especially in the gaming scene. Considering this gap, this paper proposes the development of a memory game that has audio as its main form of communication with the player, in other words, an audiogame. The product created is an {iOS} application that uses spatial audio and {VoiceOver} technologies as tools to promote accessibility, both for people with visual impairments and for sighted people. The app was tested with 18 sighted people and 1 blind person, the results are presented in this paper.},
